CC  Circular bacteriocins are antibiotic proteins made by ribosomal translation of a precursor molecular, followed by cleavage and circularization. Members of this subclass of the circular bacteriocins include circularin A from Clostridium beijerinckii, bacteriocin AS-48 from Enterococcus faecalis,  uberolysin from Streptococcus uberis, and carnocyclin A from Carnobacterium maltaromaticum. The mature circularized peptides average about 70 amino acids in size.
